27/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Paying a farewell visit to Skopje on Tuesday (26 July), outgoing KFOR commander Lieutenant General Yves de Kermabon assured officials that NATO remains committed to security in the region. Meeting with newly-appointed Macedonian Army chief Major General Miroslav Stojanovski and Defence Minister Jovan Manasijevski, de Kermabon praised the co-operation between KFOR and the Macedonian military and said he expects collaboration to continue. He added that KFOR is fully engaged in securing the Kosovo-Macedonian border from Kosovo's side. (Macedonian Government Web site - 27/07/05; A1 TV - 26/07/05)
